info.senderName: NWS NorthernIndiana (Northern Indiana and Northeastern Ohio)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued April 01 at 10:44AM EDT until April 01 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS NorthernIndiana
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM EDT THIS EVENING... * WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 60 mph. * WHERE...Portions of northern Indiana and northwest Ohio. * WHEN...Until 6 PM EDT this evening. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will negatively impact clean up efforts from last nights storms. Additional trees and powerlines may be downed. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.w * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A 58 mph wind gust has been recorded at Muncie and a wind gust of 52 mph has been recorded at Indianapolis airport. Ingredients responsible for these wind gusts will move over the warning area within the next few hours.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. Use caution if you must drive.
